==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noctuid
<hw>Noc"tu*id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>nox</ets>, <ets>noctis</ets>, night.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous moths of the family <fam>Noctuidae</fam>, or
<fam>Noctuaelitae</fam>, as the cutworm moths, and armyworm moths; -- so
called because they fly at night.</def> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Of
or pertaining to the noctuids, or family
<fam>Noctuidae</fam>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Noctule</ent>⟦br⟧
